quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  55,67,"So which of the favors of your Lord would you deny?"
  55,68,"In both of them are fruit and palm trees and pomegranates."
  55,69,"So which of the favors of your Lord would you deny?"
  56,58,"Have you seen that which you emit?{1}",footnotes:1:i.e., semen, which contains the potential for human life.
  56,59,"Is it you who creates it, or are We the Creator?"
  56,60,"We have decreed death among you, and We are not to be outdone"
  64,10,"But the ones who disbelieved and denied Our verses - those are the companions of the Fire, abiding eternally therein; and wretched is the destination."
  64,11,"No disaster strikes except by permission of Allāh. And whoever believes in Allāh - He will guide his heart. And Allāh is Knowing of all things."
  64,12,"And obey Allāh and obey the Messenger; but if you turn away - then upon Our Messenger is only [the duty of] clear notification."
  65,7,"Let a man of wealth spend from his wealth, and he whose provision is restricted - let him spend from what Allāh has given him. Allāh does not charge a soul except [according to] what He has given it. Allāh will bring about, after hardship, ease [i.e., relief]."
  65,8,"And how many a city was insolent toward the command of its Lord and His messengers, so We took it to severe account and punished it with a terrible punishment."
  65,9,"And it tasted the bad consequence of its affair [i.e., rebellion], and the outcome of its affair was loss."
  66,1,"O Prophet, why do you prohibit [yourself from] what Allāh has made lawful for you, seeking the approval of your wives? And Allāh is Forgiving and Merciful."
  66,2,"Allāh has already ordained for you [Muslims] the dissolution of your oaths.{1} And Allāh is your protector, and He is the Knowing, the Wise.",footnotes:1:By means of a kaffārah (expiation).  This is required when one is unable to fulfill an oath or when one has taken an oath which would not be pleasing to Allāh (subḥānahu wa taʿālā).  See 5:89.
  66,3,"And [remember] when the Prophet confided to one of his wives a statement; and when she informed [another] of it and Allāh showed it to him, he made known part of it and ignored a part. And when he informed her about it, she said, "